<p>Follow these authorization procedures when transferring a POWER case from one (1) DFS-FO to another.</p>
<p>A. The transferring Benefit Specialist has primary responsibility for a transfer between field offices because s/he will have knowledge concerning the transfer of the POWER case.</p>
<p>B. Transferring child support and work program action center staff will contact the receiving contract office to advise an open POWER case will be transferred.;</p>
<p>C. Process the performance payment when the client has contacted the receiving DFS-FO by the 15th and verified and met all eligibility factors, including the performance requirements.</p>
<p>D. Authorize the $1 nonpayment status when the client has not contacted the receiving DFS-FO by the 15th to update the changes and met the performance requirements.</p>
<p>E. Terminate the case when there is a loss of contact for a full performance period and generate the appropriate closure notice (see Table V).</p>
